11.3 Read about Lisa's journey to Madrid. Put the verbs in the correct form.

1 fly, 2 get, 3 have, 4 leave, 5 drive, 6 get, 7 park, 8 walk, 9 check, 10 have, 11 wait, 12 depart, 13 arrive, 14 take


Last Tuesday Lisa (flew) from London to Madrid. She (got) up. 
at 6 o'clock in the morning and (3) had a cup of coffee.
At 6.30 she (4) lefy
home and (5) drove to the airport.
When she (6) got there,
she (7) parked the car, 
walked (8) to the airport building, 
and (9) checked in. 
Then she (10) had breakfast at a cafe
and (11) waited for her flight. 
The plane (12) departed on time and 
(13) arrived in Madrid two hours later. 
Finally she (14) took a taxi from the airport to her hotel in the centre of Madrid.

11.4 Write sentences about the past (yesterday / last week etc.)

1. James always goes to work by car. Yesterday he went to work by car
2. Rachel often loses her keys. She lost her keys last week.
3. Kate meets her friends every evening. She met her friends yesterday evening.
4. I buy a newspaper every day. Yesterday I bought a newspapper
5. We often go to the cinema at weekends. Last Sunday we went to the cinema.
6. I eat an orange every day. Yesterday I ate an orange.
7. Tom always has a shower in the morning. This morning he had a shower.
8. Our friends often come to see us. They last Friday  came to see us.

11.5 Write sentences about what you did yesterday.

1. i went to the theatre.
2. i saw tv.
3. i had dinner 9 o' cook.
4. my mom broke the living room wall.
5. my parents argue about football.
6. i ate chicken for lunch.

